The paper deals with the computational and mechanism design aspects of resource allocation, specifically in the context of healthcare. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories, which deal with optimization and decision-making problems. The paper also discusses the endogenous emergence of waiting times and the dynamics between hospitals and patients, which suggests that it may also belong to the Complex Systems (cs.CE) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses potential policy implications, which suggests that it may also belong to the Health (cs.HE) sub-category.
